Try to find which bathroom appliance might be the source of wet patches or drips (shower, bath, toilet). Turn on each appliance in turn, checking the drips or the wet space to see if it worsens with any particular appliance. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/bd/Troubleshoot-a-Leaking-Upstairs-Bathroom-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Troubleshoot-a-Leaking-Upstairs-Bathroom-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/b/bd/Troubleshoot-a-Leaking-Upstairs-Bathroom-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/aid2647718-v4-728px-Troubleshoot-a-Leaking-Upstairs-Bathroom-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"485","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
